271
00:15:33,870 --> 00:15:35,660
Let's leave it to Hayate.

272
00:15:35,660 --> 00:15:37,510
He's in great condition today.

273
00:15:37,510 --> 00:15:38,220
Whee...

274
00:15:40,870 --> 00:15:45,120
Revenge? It's your own fault for losing control!

275
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:50,660
Shut up! Because I lost to you, I... I lost everything!

276
00:15:51,380 --> 00:15:55,430
Eight, you have to become the world's best nursing robot.

277
00:15:56,460 --> 00:16:01,710
I did tests after tests to meet the scientist's standard.

278
00:16:01,710 --> 00:16:04,030
It was boring, but I did my best.

279
00:16:04,030 --> 00:16:05,280
Because...

280
00:16:06,230 --> 00:16:07,950
Are you doing okay over there, Eight?

281
00:16:07,950 --> 00:16:10,320
Because she was there.

282
00:16:11,290 --> 00:16:12,450
Eight!

283
00:16:12,450 --> 00:16:13,640
You're amazing!

284
00:16:13,640 --> 00:16:16,050
You're so cool, Eight!

285
00:16:16,050 --> 00:16:17,310
Eight~

286
00:16:17,310 --> 00:16:19,460
Beat the Vandel ******.

287
00:16:19,460 --> 00:16:21,190
She was everything to me.

288
00:16:21,190 --> 00:16:22,840
But that day!

289
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:25,900
What? Eight lost to a trash among humans?

290
00:16:25,900 --> 00:16:27,820
Defeated in such a way, too?

291
00:16:27,820 --> 00:16:29,790
My nursing missiles were ineffective?

292
00:16:30,140 --> 00:16:31,140
Chief...

293
00:16:31,370 --> 00:16:33,100
Then I guess we'll terminate development.

294
00:16:34,620 --> 00:16:38,860
Beside, it's wrong to try and let robots do everything.

295
00:16:38,860 --> 00:16:41,660
Plus the design and the functions were so lame.

296
00:16:41,660 --> 00:16:43,280
Ch-Chief!

297
00:16:44,070 --> 00:16:48,890
I lost everything as such
and got thrown away as noncombustible trash.

298
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:55,060
Chief has her own world and is forgetful, so she forgot about me...

299
00:16:55,060 --> 00:16:58,570
...and was working on developing a new nursing robot.

300
00:16:58,570 --> 00:17:01,330
But... But my heart won't be salvaged with that.

301
00:17:01,890 --> 00:17:05,170
In order for me to get her smile back,

302
00:17:05,450 --> 00:17:10,950
Hayate, I need to beat you and that twin-tailed brat!

303
00:17:17,750 --> 00:17:21,010
Wh-What? You're only a pet.

304
00:17:21,010 --> 00:17:22,590
Shut up, you scrap ****!

305
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:28,140
I don't care what you do to the miserable, stupid, human trash, debt-ridden butler,

306
00:17:28,690 --> 00:17:32,000
but I won't forgive anyone who tries to hurt the Lady.

307
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:34,950
You're right; Our Lady is selfish, self-centered, and rude.

308
00:17:34,950 --> 00:17:37,890
Her acts are based on whims, and she never admits mistakes.

309
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:40,660
She's tougher than others,
doesn't know the real world, is cheeky,

310
00:17:40,660 --> 00:17:44,160
but can't sleep alone at night.

311
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:47,900
She proclaims to have high athleticism when she doesn't.

312
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:50,390
As such, she's a failure as a human,

313
00:17:50,970 --> 00:17:53,120
but she's the one who saved my life.

314
00:17:53,300 --> 00:17:54,920
What's wrong, Nagi?

315
00:17:54,920 --> 00:17:59,090
I don't know, but I feel like someone just spoke badly of me.

316
00:17:59,370 --> 00:18:04,260
So, I'll destroy everything that becomes Our Lady's enemy.

317
00:18:06,190 --> 00:18:06,960
Wait!

318
00:18:07,410 --> 00:18:09,890
Hayate! Y-You...

319
00:18:09,890 --> 00:18:13,170
You're going to shield him when he tried to kill you?

320
00:18:15,160 --> 00:18:18,740
I know the sadness of being abandoned and forsaken.

321
00:18:19,970 --> 00:18:25,620
But, because there was a person who saved us...

322
00:18:27,550 --> 00:18:29,550
...we are here today!

323
00:18:30,050 --> 00:18:32,520
You understand that, too, Tama.

324
00:18:35,310 --> 00:18:37,260
So you...

325
00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:41,250
So you understand how I feel?

326
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:44,310
Since I've gone through a similar experience.

327
00:18:44,700 --> 00:18:45,700
I see.

328
00:18:45,970 --> 00:18:48,280
If you understand my feeling,

329
00:18:48,280 --> 00:18:51,580
then be killed by me!

330
00:18:51,840 --> 00:18:54,120
The sound's getting louder.

331
00:18:54,120 --> 00:18:59,600
According to the report from Security, the nursing robot from sometime ago is here for revenge and is causing a rampage.

332
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:02,350
Are you sure you don't need to go save him?

333
00:19:02,350 --> 00:19:05,060
Hayate won't lose against someone he fought once before.

334
00:19:05,230 --> 00:19:09,000
But apparently he versioned up to 8.1 and powered up.

335
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:11,770
8.1? That's just adding a patch file.

336
00:19:11,770 --> 00:19:15,800
Besides, Hayate is fighting for me.

337
00:19:16,060 --> 00:19:17,780
Doesn't that turn you on a little?

338
00:19:17,780 --> 00:19:20,270
I hope he hasn't turned into a ball of flame.

339
00:19:21,810 --> 00:19:26,220
Take this, my new ultimate mode that came with the new version!

340
00:19:26,220 --> 00:19:28,610
Mosquito Destroy Mode!

341
00:19:30,560 --> 00:19:33,050
Japan's summer is filled with mosquitoes.

342
00:19:33,050 --> 00:19:37,260
It's a necessary mode for providing the nursed one a pleasant sleep.

343
00:19:37,750 --> 00:19:39,850
Um, how about we call it quits?

344
00:19:39,850 --> 00:19:42,230
You won't win against us with that.

345
00:19:42,230 --> 00:19:45,730
Shut up! I must have her-

346
00:19:46,530 --> 00:19:47,500
Eight!

347
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:50,070
Th-That voice... It can't be...

348
00:19:50,970 --> 00:19:52,440
C-Chief!

349
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:55,490
Eight, thank goodness, you were here.

350
00:19:55,490 --> 00:19:58,680
I remembered about you.

351
00:19:58,950 --> 00:20:02,080
S-So? What did you come here now for?

352
00:20:02,530 --> 00:20:05,020
I'm already abandoned by you.

353
00:20:05,020 --> 00:20:06,010
I'm sorry.

354
00:20:06,010 --> 00:20:07,610
But you got it all wrong.

355
00:20:07,610 --> 00:20:08,990
There was a slight mistake.

356
00:20:10,180 --> 00:20:11,450
Chief...

357
00:20:11,450 --> 00:20:15,630
I was thoughtless and threw you out as noncombustible...

358
00:20:16,010 --> 00:20:18,560
I'm really sorry...

359
00:20:18,810 --> 00:20:19,900
Chief...

360
00:20:20,840 --> 00:20:22,860
I was wrong.

361
00:20:22,860 --> 00:20:24,470
It's fine now.

362
00:20:24,470 --> 00:20:28,240
Eight, you are not noncombustible trash.

363
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:30,900
It's so tear-jerking.

364
00:20:30,900 --> 00:20:31,840
Yes.

365
00:20:32,020 --> 00:20:33,540
You're oversized trash.

366
00:20:37,050 --> 00:20:40,140
Hello, we're the ones you called for.

367
00:20:40,140 --> 00:20:41,630
Please take care of it.

368
00:20:41,630 --> 00:20:42,600
Is this it?

369
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:43,920
Yes, take it away, please.

370
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:45,060
Ch-Chief?

371
00:20:45,060 --> 00:20:47,210
Do you know there's a law for recycling household appliances?

372
00:20:47,210 --> 00:20:50,350
You're not supposed to throw
large electronic devices away on the street.

373
00:20:50,350 --> 00:20:54,750
But don't worry, they'll take you apart and trash you properly.

374
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:56,270
Bye now.

375
00:20:57,990 --> 00:21:01,590
We're lucky Milady was the one that picked us up.

376
00:21:01,590 --> 00:21:02,170
Yeah.

377
00:21:02,420 --> 00:21:05,090
Wait, this isn't the right way to end this at all!

378
00:21:05,090 --> 00:21:08,060
We need to do something to save Eight!

379
00:21:08,060 --> 00:21:09,650
But how?

380
00:21:10,940 --> 00:21:12,840
Leave it to me.

381
00:21:15,150 --> 00:21:16,600
Hey, this Makimura?

382
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:18,950
It's me, Sanzenin Nagi.

383
00:21:18,950 --> 00:21:23,200
Listen, you mustn't break that rundown robot.

384
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:24,200
That's right.

385
00:21:25,410 --> 00:21:26,380
Didn't I sound just like her?

386
00:21:27,040 --> 00:21:29,300
I never knew you had such a trick!

387
00:21:29,810 --> 00:21:31,820
Hayate! Hayate!

388
00:21:31,820 --> 00:21:35,070
Did you use Kamehame** to defeat him last night?

389
00:21:35,320 --> 00:21:37,710
No, I can't use that yet.

390
00:21:37,710 --> 00:21:40,810
By the way, soon after leaving the mansion,

391
00:21:41,080 --> 00:21:43,780
Makimura-san, please go out with me!

392
00:21:44,370 --> 00:21:46,250
What? Sure.

393
00:21:46,250 --> 00:21:49,210
Eight started a new life.

394
00:21:49,210 --> 00:21:54,890
Next time, we'll fight against the lord of the lake to be the champion of the Slympics.

395
00:23:30,220 --> 00:23:30,920
Nagi and...

396
00:23:31,380 --> 00:23:32,520
Isumi's...

397
00:23:32,520 --> 00:23:34,260
Butler Network!

398
00:23:35,130 --> 00:23:40,440
Last week, Isumi couldn't say anything about the song, so today, I'm here to support her.

399
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:42,180
Thank you, Nagi.

400
00:23:42,180 --> 00:23:49,140
So Isumi, this song is, you know, slow like you, and then thickened and has fat added and all cooked together.

401
00:23:49,140 --> 00:23:53,110
I don't think that made any sense.

402
00:23:53,110 --> 00:23:55,750
Anyway, it's a nice song.

403
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:58,530
Thank you, Nagi.

404
00:23:58,920 --> 00:23:59,920
Bye bye.

405
00:24:00,830 --> 00:24:01,990
This time, it's fishing.

406
00:24:01,990 --> 00:24:02,920
We'll catch all we can!

407
00:24:02,920 --> 00:24:04,200
First, it's fly fishing!

408
00:24:04,200 --> 00:24:06,690
Fly fishing? Isn't that challenging?

409
00:24:06,690 --> 00:24:09,790
In "I Love Fishing. Sanpei", Sanpei-kun was catching one fish after another using flies.

410
00:24:09,790 --> 00:24:12,120
There isn't anything I can't do when Sanpei-kun can.

411
00:24:12,120 --> 00:24:15,580
Milady, it's not good to mix manga and reality.

412
00:24:15,580 --> 00:24:16,640
Hit, hit, hit!

413
00:24:16,640 --> 00:24:18,120
DAAAHH!

414
00:24:18,120 --> 00:24:19,590
Next time on Hayate no Gotoku.

415
00:24:19,590 --> 00:24:22,940
Who Came Up With the Onomatopoeia "Kapo~n"? It's Amazing.

416
00:24:22,940 --> 00:24:25,940
I didn't expect Hayate to come so close the moment we were alone.

417
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:28,450
The entertainment level will be in the red zone as usual.

